ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project delivers a data-driven framework to analyze, forecast, and economically evaluate natural gas prices using historical market data.
The objective is to support long-term storage and contract pricing decisions by modeling seasonality, trends, and volatility in natural gas markets.

The solution mirrors how energy trading desks and strategy teams evaluate price curves for storage optimization and risk-aware planning.

ğŸ¯ Business Objective

Energy firms rely on accurate forward price expectations to decide:

When to buy natural gas

Whether to store it

When to sell to maximize margins

This project answers:

â€œGiven historical price behavior, what is the expected price of natural gas at any future date, and how can this be used to value storage decisions?â€

