ğŸ§  Modeling Approach
ğŸ“ˆ Forecasting Technique: Holt-Winters Exponential Smoothing

Why Holt-Winters?

Explicitly models level, trend, and seasonality

Robust for short- to medium-term energy price forecasting

Widely used in industry and financial time-series analysis

Model Intuition (Simplified):

Level: Baseline price

Trend: Directional movement over time

Seasonality: Monthly recurring patterns

Forecast = Level + Trend + Seasonality

ğŸ“‰ Forecast Output

Generated a 12-month forward price curve

Enables:

Indicative long-term pricing

Strategic planning for storage contracts

Designed for decision support, not high-frequency trading

ğŸ¦ Storage Valuation Framework

The project extends beyond forecasting into economic value creation:

ğŸ’¡ Storage Logic

Buy gas during low-price (summer) periods

Store the gas

Sell during high-price (winter) periods

ğŸ’° Valuation Formula
Storage Value = (Expected Future Sell Price âˆ’ Purchase Price) Ã— Volume âˆ’ Storage Costs


This mirrors real-world energy trading and infrastructure valuation models.

ğŸ“Œ Illustrative Use Case

Purchase natural gas during forecasted seasonal lows

Withdraw and sell during forecasted winter peaks

Use the forward curve to estimate expected margins and justify storage decisions

